<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/50201AJQJMNKPVNTVBTBMSCMBRSMTGJSS> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "CRASH TEST DUMMIES ";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$79 All Seats</span><span><br/></span>Includes fees & tax<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With one of the most recognizable voices in Canadian music history, alternative rock band <span class=\"BoldText\">Crash Test Dummies</span> are a 3-time Grammy nominated and JUNO Award-winning group, who soared to the top of the worldwide charts in the early-90’s with hits <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Mmm, Mmm, Mmm, Mmm”</span></span> and <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Superman’s Song”</span></span>. Their cover of <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">“The Ballad of Peter Pumpkinhead”</span></span> was a highlight of the soundtrack to the blockbuster film, “Dumb and Dumber”, while simultaneously reaching #4 on the US Top 100 album charts. All of their releases keep the same folk-hued, alternative spirit of their early sound, centering around the distinct baritone of frontman <span class=\"BoldText\">Brad Roberts</span> and <span class=\"BoldText\">Ellen Reid’s</span> folk-rock fusion.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>After a twenty-year hiatus, the <span class=\"BoldText\">Crash Test Dummies</span> reunited in 2018 for a two-week tour to celebrate their most successful album <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">“God Shuffled His Feet”</span></span>. The overwhelming reception to these shows led to continuous touring across two continents, with sold-out shows across the US, Canada, the UK, Germany, Austria and the Netherlands.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The band returns to the UK in fall 2026 for an extensive tour, then an extensive West Coast of Canada Swing—including Vernon’s own VDPAC--to end 2026 before heading “down under” for a return tour of Australia in early 2027, following their sold-out shows in 2025!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The dynamic and high-energy stage show features the band’s most iconic songs, performed by original members <span class=\"BoldText\">Brad Roberts, Ellen Reid, Dan Roberts</span> and <span class=\"BoldText\">Mitch Dorge</span>. Joining them are long-standing guitarist <span class=\"BoldText\">Stuart Cameron</span> and relative newcomer <span class=\"BoldText\">Leith Fleming-Smith</span>, Canada’s keyboard whiz-kid.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Special Guest <span class=\"BoldText\">Logan Richard</span> is one of music’s rarest creatures—a compelling and diverse songwriter who also shreds. This PEI-born-and-based artist has built his reputation as a deft, genre-fluid songsmith and peerless hired gun for some of Canada’s most exciting musicians. His new full-length, <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Character Traits”</span></span>, collects the undeniable evidence of Richard’s talents under his own name as he navigates slick pop, spacey R&B, and soulful folk.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Don’t miss Canada’s own <span class=\"BoldText\">Crash Test Dummies</span>, with Special Guest, <span class=\"BoldText\">Logan Richard</span> an unforgettable VDPAC Signature Concert Series experience!<span><br/></span>
""";
