  schema:name "Humpty Dumpty - The Musical";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$23.50 Per Person</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Seaton’s 27th Street Theatre</span> has worked “9 to 5” turning the classic British Pantomime, <span class=\"BoldText\">Humpty Dumpty</span> into a fun new country and western themed musical. The story is set in Nursery Rhyme County where the Heroes are kind, the Villains are mischievous, the Sidekicks are silly, and the Dames are well…. Dames!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This Pantomime is full of song, dance, inside jokes, slapstick comedy, and audience participation! As <span class=\"BoldText\">Humpty Dumpty</span> is western themed, <span class=\"BoldText\">the audiences are invited to don their best western wear and join in on the fun!</span> Boo the Villains, Cheer the Heroes, and warn the actors if something is creeping up on them with the classic screams of “LOOK BEHIND YOU!”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The<span class=\"BoldText\"> 27th Street Theatre</span> is excited to have a live band for this production, led by grade 12 student, Dylan Green. Student choreographers Ashley Burke (grade 12) and Cora Iverson (grade 10) have done an extraordinary job of integrating old time waltzes, square dance, and line dance throughout the show.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Come out and have a frolickin' good time!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">ALLERGY WARNING</span> Clean, organic straw is placed throughout the stage, and near some of the seats. Please, take your allergy medication if you are allergic to hay, straw, or have seasonal allergies.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-19T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
