<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/46201AMLCVHRCMSRMCBPBJCBDJSGKTGPC> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Matt Dusk - A Very Sinatra Christmas";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$59.00 Per Person</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & Charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Matt Dusk</span> is one of Canada’s most celebrated vocalists, a modern entertainer bridging classic showmanship with today’s viral music culture.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Backed by a powerhouse big band, Dusk will transport audiences to the golden age of swing, blending timeless holiday classics with the unforgettable style of the one-and-only Frank Sinatra. From <span class=\"ItalicText\">“It’s the Most Wonderful Time of the Year”</span> to <span class=\"ItalicText\">“The Christmas Song”</span>, A Very Sinatra Christmas is brimming with nostalgia, glamour, and holiday spirit - perfect for fans of classic music and unforgettable live entertainment.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“There’s nothing like the magic of the holidays - and no better way to celebrate than with the music of Sinatra and a big band,” says Dusk. “Expect a swinging night of Christmas favourites, timeless charm, and maybe even a little snowfall on stage!”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In 2026, Dusk has experienced a major resurgence with a new generation of fans through viral reimagined pop and K-pop covers, including standout renditions of global hits like <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Golden”</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Five Nights at Freddy’s.”</span> In just three months, Matt has earned over 40M views (and counting) across Instagram, TikTok, and YouTube, earning him a place at the forefront of the modern viral crooner revival among a new generation of globally trending vocal performers.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With a 25-year career spanning 14 critically acclaimed studio albums and over one million albums sold worldwide, Dusk’s international success is attributed to his smooth, soulful voice and his remarkable ability to merge the timeless elegance of classic jazz with fresh, contemporary sounds. This unique blend has made him a beloved figure on stages around the world. Rising to international attention with his 2004 debut Two Shots, Dusk quickly became known for reinventing timeless swing and pop standards for contemporary audiences, touring extensively across North America, Europe, and Asia.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>His discography includes multiple Gold and Platinum-certified albums, and chart-topping radio hits in Canada, Japan, and France. A graduate of St. Michael’s Choir School and a protégé of jazz legend Oscar Peterson at York University, Dusk has earned multiple JUNO, ADISQ, and international award nominations, along with acclaimed television appearances including FOX’s The Casino and Hallmark’s Deck the Halls on Cherry Lane. Praised by Billboard, Jazz Times, and the Los Angeles Times for his Sinatra-esque swagger and modern sensibility, Matt Dusk continues to redefine what a contemporary crooner can be—timeless, stylish, and digitally viral.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“Crooners like Toronto’s Matt Dusk has taken what he has learned from the greats and molded it for a modern audience.” -LA Times<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“Blending distinctly Sinatra-esque swagger, Dusk is waist deep in grandiose arrangements that are dripping with Sin City excess and turns the clock back some four decades with excellence.” -Jazz Times<span><br/></span>
""";
