<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/68201ATPHPGBHMDNSHHSTPHBMQBRQBLST> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "NOCCA - Aurora Piano Trio";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$45.00 Adult<span><br/></span></span><span class=\"BoldText\">$25.00 Student</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The <span class=\"BoldText\">Aurora Piano Trio</span> has already been praised for its passion, exuberance and lyricism and sensational performances. Violinist Yuel Yawney and cellist, Sungyong Lim, members of the Borealis String Quartet, joined together with acclaimed pianist, Libby Yu to form Canada's most exciting new ensemble, the <span class=\"BoldText\">Aurora Piano Trio</span>. Each of the members of the Trio has performed around the world and brings their extensive chamber music experience together creating an ensemble of the highest caliber.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Founded in 2019 and mentored by the great Canadian impresario, George Zukerman, the Trio is already garnering much critical acclaim and is taking the Canadian music scene by storm. Debuting for the Whistler Chamber Music Society in the Trio's first season as part of a Western Canadian tour, the remaining engagements were cancelled due to COVID. Since 2021, the Trio has begun rebooking engagements and that September was the season opening concert to a sold-out audience for the Cafe Classico Series at the Langley Community Music School. The Trio also had numerous performances at the Music by the Sea Festival in Victoria to standing ovations and later in Vancouver at the Orpheum ANNEX and the Centre Stage at Surrey City Hall. Since then, the <span class=\"BoldText\">Aurora Piano Trio</span> performed numerous concerts touring around BC.<span><br/></span>
""";
