<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/39801ATJCSCVLGHGKQJHSGGHGSRBRSCPQ> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Orchestral Rock Odyssey";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$39.75</span><span class=\"BoldText\"> Rows A-C</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Rows D-M and AA-CC<span><br/></span>$76.50 Adult<span><br/></span>$68.75 Senior 65+<span><br/></span></span><span class=\"BoldText\">$39.75 Youth 24y + Under</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Rows N-P + DD-JJ<span><br/></span></span><span class=\"BoldText\">$68.25 Adult<span><br/></span>$60.00 Senior 65+<span><br/></span>$33.25 Youth 24y + Under</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>BACK BY POPULAR DEMAND! Following on the heels of 2 sold-out tours through the Okanagan, The Gary Cable Project returns to Vernon with ORCHESTRAL ROCK ODYSSEY, with the Okanagan Pops Orchestra and Project Singers. Join us for a spectacular night of incredible music, performed by some of the top musicians in the country. A 9-piece pop/rock band, along with a symphony orchestra and vocal chorus, will perform some of the greatest songs every recorded --Styx, Elton John, Foreigner, the Bee Gees, Earth Wind & Fire, Whitney Houston, Simon & Garfunkel, and so much more! This is the one concert you do not want to miss...<span><br/></span>
""";
