		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Okanagan Symphony Orchestra presents a rare opportunity to hear the tuba as a solo instrument — jazz legend Wynton Marsalis’s vibrant and genre-blending Concerto for Tuba shines in the hands of Chris Lee, principal tubist of the National Arts Centre Orchestra. Paired with the folk-infused lyricism of Dvořák’s Symphony No. 8, and a collaboration with the Okanagan Symphony Youth Orchestra, this OSO performance offers colour, rhythmic drive, and orchestral vitality.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Conductor - </span>Julian Pellicano<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Guest artist/instrument - </span>Chris Lee, <span class=\"ItalicText\">tuba<span><br/></span></span>OSYO Side-by-Side performance<span class=\"ItalicText\"><span><br/></span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Program</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Opening Selection: OSYO / OSO Side-by-Side<span><br/></span>Wynton Marsalis: Tuba Concerto<span><br/></span>Dvořák: Symphony No. 8, op.88 in G major<span><br/></span>
