<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/46801ACDBKCSKJDBSGRJBRPHCJBLCKVCG> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Screening Night";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$16 Admit</span><span><br/></span>*includes all fees & tax<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">The Okanagan 48 Hour Film Project</span> returns for its 4th annual screening at Powerhouse Theatre in Vernon on Friday, June 5, 2026. Doors open at 5pm with the screening starting at 6pm.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Over one wild weekend, filmmaking teams from across the Okanagan were handed a genre, a character, a prop, and a line of dialogue, then given just 48 hours to write, shoot, edit, and deliver a complete short film. The results are now ready for the big screen, and you're invited to see what local creativity can pull off under the tightest of deadlines.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Expect comedy, drama, horror, sci-fi, and everything in between, all made by your neighbours, friends, and the Okanagan film community. Come cheer on the teams and celebrate independent filmmaking.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>More info at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.48hourfilm.com/okanagan\">okgn48.ca</a>
""";
