<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/38801AQDNRKLTDJNRGTHNNSDTQVMLRTCD> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Barra MacNeils 40th Anniversary Tour";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$49 Per Person</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For more than three decades, Cape Breton-based family group The Barra MacNeils, as \"Canada's Celtic Folk Ambassadors\" have been thrilling audiences of all ages, near and far, with their sparkling repertoire, vocals, instrumental prowess and vibrant showmanship.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The MacNeil siblings are widely regarded as one of the greatest live concert acts in the Celtic music world. Hailing from Sydney Mines, Nova Scotia, the family is deeply rooted in Celtic music, culture, dance, language and history.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>They have released 17 albums and garnered 15 East Coast Music Award nominations, winning 5 ECMA and two JUNO Awards. This year they completed their 25th annual coast-to-coast \"An East Coast Christmas\" concert tour that sold-out the VDPAC in November 2025.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Their live concert experience brings so much more to the stage than most live acts ever can. Multiple lead vocalists, beautiful sibling harmonies, flawless instrumental prowess on a wide variety of acoustic, stringed, percussion and wind instruments, blended with dancing, storytelling, Gaelic songs and a journey through an ancient, romantic culture; it is family entertainment of the highest order!
""";
