<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/58001AHVKTQNTHCMDPHPJMNRHLKSPJCPS> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Dark Side of the Moon - In Concert";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$99.75 - Rows A – C<span><br/></span>$89.75 - Rows D – J and AA to CC<span><br/></span>$79.75 - Rows K – P<span><br/></span></span><span class=\"BoldText\">$69.75 - Rows DD – KK</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Including fees & charges</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Celebrate the 50th anniversary of Pink Floyd's legendary concert tour with original band members Graham Broad, Mark Lennon, Chester Kamen and Roger Waters' son, Harry Waters, as well as Berlin Pink Floyd & Echoes. A homage to the greatest rock opera of all time with musicians from the original Pink Floyd and Roger Waters tours plus the band. Pink Floyd's best-selling album live with the original band members! The Big Concert in the Clouds, Money, Us and Them, Time - immerse yourself in the timeless soundscape that reshaped the landscape of rock music. From captivating melodies to deep lyrics - experience Pink Floyd's magnum opus like never before. Take a journey inside the rock phenomenon that continues to captivate audiences around the world.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With an approval rating on social media of 99.7 percent, this concert series is considered the most popular in the world.<span><br/></span>
""";
