<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/63001AJJHHCCDTKKSDNHNCJHVRPDPDKLT> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Vagina Monologues";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$50.00 Per Person</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Mature Content Ages 16+<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>When <span class=\"BoldText\">The Vagina Monologues</span> first premiered in 1994, it changed the cultural conversation around women’s voices, bodies, sexuality, trauma, pleasure, and power forever.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Created by acclaimed Playwright and Activist V from dozens of real interviews with women of diverse ages, backgrounds, and experiences, this groundbreaking play shattered taboos with extraordinary humour, honesty, compassion, and courage; becoming one of the most influential and widely performed works of modern theatre.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>At times laugh-out-loud funny, deeply intimate, heartbreaking, and triumphant, The Vagina Monologues explores the full complexity of womanhood through a series of powerful stories that are raw, wise, fearless, and profoundly human.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With wit and vulnerability, the play invites audiences into conversations that are often hidden behind silence and shame, transforming them into moments of connection, empathy, liberation, and joy. More than three decades after its debut, its message continues to resonate with audiences around the world.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>One’s Own Theatre Ltd. is proud to bring this iconic work to Vernon in a bold new production staged within the unique atmosphere of Headbones Gallery.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All proceeds from this production will directly support the growth of One’s Own Theatre Ltd.: Vernon’s first professional theatre company devoted to producing exceptional live theatre that centers women’s stories and creates professional opportunities for women artists, creators, and theatre-makers.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Audience members are also invited to stay tuned for One’s Own Theatre’s inaugural main-stage production, coming to the Powerhouse Theatre in December 2026.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Advisory:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">This production contains mature themes, sexual content, strong language, and references to violence and abuse. Recommended for audiences 16+</span>.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-08-20T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/ticketseller/files/4b87d32f-65e2-46d1-8e43-5312a8ede0ff.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/ticketseller/location/5001ABHHSRBTQRMRKVQTDCNNRTMMJHMGD>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/ticketseller/organization/one's-own-theatre>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36865709;
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-08-20T21:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

